+  canonicalization choices,
+  and substantively different modeling choices;
+- for each candidate, decide which parts of its criterion, packet object,
+  threshold language, and downstream gate must be invariant under true exact
+  symmetries;
+- decide whether any dependence on canonicalization choices is acceptable under
+  the Step-1 and Step-2 frozen policy, or whether it reveals representation
+  instability;
+- decide whether sensitivity to substantive modeling choices is merely a
+  use-case limitation or instead a fatal sign of circularity, threshold
+  gerrymandering, or importation of Tao's averaged mechanism by hand;
+- produce a candidate-by-candidate robustness matrix and a step verdict saying
+  whether Chain Step 4 is now well-posed, or whether the branch should stop
+  with a named negative failure bucket.
+
+Do **not** run the normalized anti-circuit / pro-circuit packet dossier yet.
+That belongs to Chain Step 4. Minimal packet examples are allowed only if they
+are needed to decide a robustness question about symmetry, canonicalization, or
+modeling-choice dependence.
+
+## Frozen Commitments You Must Inherit
+
+All robustness judgments in this step must inherit the earlier freezes:
+
+- the only candidates under audit are the three Step-2 promoted notions;
+- the packet object remains the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical
