+# Step 4 Goal: Chain Step 4 Test Surviving Candidates On Normalized Exact Packets And Parameter Families
+
+## Mission Context
+
+**Mission:** Exact NS No-Near-Closed Tao Circuit
+
+**Active chain:**
+`Canonical Winning Chain - Co-Evolving Definition Freeze and Exact Interaction Audit With Invariant Downstream Gates`
+
+**Why this step exists now:** `step-003` succeeded at the branch's third gate.
+It did not kill the candidate family. Instead it found that
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+and
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+survive as
+`stable after canonicalization`,
+while
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`
+survives as
+`use-case-limited but honest`.
+Mission control therefore keeps the current chain active. The next unresolved
+bottleneck is no longer definition sharpness or robustness discipline. It is
+whether those surviving notions still say something real when forced onto
+explicit normalized exact packets and parameter families, including both
+anti-circuit and pro-circuit cases.
+
+## This Step Covers
+
+This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 4 only**.
+
+You must do all of the following, and only the following:
+
+- test the three surviving candidates:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`;
+- choose explicit normalized exact packets or explicitly parameterized packet
+  families on the frozen one-bridge role-labeled helical packet object;
+- include both anti-circuit and pro-circuit examples;
+- include adverse cases already known to matter:
+  `Beltrami cancellation`,
+  `mirror-mode completion`,
+  `nearly degenerate triads`,
+  and
+  `tiny trigger modes`;
+- include cases favorable to the opposite conclusion:
+  `engineered helical sign patterns`,
+  `sparse triad geometries`,
+  `scale-separated packets`,
+  and families where leakage exists but may be dynamically negligible;
+- precommit quantitative pass/fail criteria for each candidate before reading
+  off outcomes;
+- use hard admissibility filters and retain a non-aggregated diagnostic vector
+  for each candidate on each tested family;
+- decide for each candidate whether the exact-packet dossier says
+  `survives`,
+  `fails`,
+  or
+  `remains ambiguous`,
+  with one named reason;
+- decide whether Chain Step 5 is now well-posed as a single honest repair pass,
+  or whether the branch instead stops here with the sharpest earned negative
+  memo.
+
+Do **not** run the Step-5 repair pass yet. That belongs to Chain Step 5. Do
+**not** reopen broad planning or substitute a new candidate family. Minimal
+normalization choices are allowed only if they are frozen before outcomes and
+kept inside the Step-1 through Step-3 packet discipline.
+
+## Frozen Commitments You Must Inherit
+
+All exact-packet tests in this step must inherit the earlier freezes:
+
+- the packet object remains the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical
+  packet family with mandatory conjugate completion;
+- the shared Tao-like interaction core remains
+  `A -> B`,
+  `A -> C`,
+  `B,C -> C`,
+  `C,A <-> D`,
+  `D,D -> E`;
+- the forced spectator classes remain:
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  `cross`;
+- each candidate keeps its Step-2 criterion, sign sheet, amplitude anchor,
+  phase anchor or equivalent gauge, fixed finite activation window, and named
+  downstream gate;
+- the Step-3 robustness verdicts remain in force:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure` and `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+  are canonicalization-stable survivors,
+  while `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` is a narrower admission-filter survivor;
+- later negative conclusions are still allowed to land only in:
+  `not well-defined`,
+  `not robust after canonicalization`,
+  or `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`.
+
+No test may rescue a candidate by changing packet semantics, spectator
+partition, interaction currency, sign sheet, phase bookkeeping, time window,
+or threshold values after outcomes are seen. No test may import Tao's averaged
+freedoms by hand.
+
+## Required Deliverables
+
+Produce all of the following inside `RESULTS.md`:
+
+1. **Normalized test-family ledger**
+   - list the anti-circuit packet families and pro-circuit packet families
+     actually tested;
+   - state the normalization choices and why they are allowed under the frozen
+     packet-sheet policy;
+   - state which adverse and favorable cases each family is meant to cover.
+
+2. **Predeclared pass/fail sheet**
+   - for each candidate, state the exact thresholds, tolerances, or event
+     conditions being used on this step;
+   - state the non-aggregated diagnostic vector that will be recorded on each
+     tested family;
+   - state the no-retuning discipline explicitly.
+
+3. **Exact-packet dossier**
+   - for each tested family, record the exact interaction data used:
+     helical coefficient/sign ledger,
+     desired-channel forcing,
+     classwise spectator forcing,
+     and event-time traces where relevant;
+   - for each candidate on each family, report whether the candidate passes,
+     fails, or stays ambiguous under the predeclared sheet;
+   - separate obstruction-facing evidence from construction-facing evidence.
+
+4. **Candidate comparison table**
+   - classify each candidate after Step 4 as exactly one of:
+     `survives`,
+     `fails`,
+     or
+     `remains ambiguous`;
+   - give one short reason tied to the tested packet dossier rather than a
+     slogan;
+   - state whether the result pushes the candidate toward
+     `not robust after canonicalization`
+     or
+     `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`,
+     if a negative drift is earned.
+
+5. **Step verdict**
+   - state whether Chain Step 5 is now well-posed;
+   - if yes, list which candidates move into the one honest repair pass and the
+     exact issue each repair is allowed to address;
+   - if no, state plainly that the branch should stop here and name the earned
+     negative memo:
+     either an untestable-object result under this step's kill condition, or
+     one of the allowed mission failure buckets if fully earned already.
+
+## Exploration Scope
+
+Use **2-3 explorations total** unless a kill condition fires early.
+
+The work should rely first on the local record already frozen by the previous
+steps:
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN-HISTORY.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/winning-chain.md`
+- the inherited `atlas-source/` packet already used in Steps 1 through 3
+
+Do **not** reopen broad mission planning. Do **not** resurvey Tao's paper
+generally. Do **not** generalize beyond explicit packet families or
+parameterized families that remain concrete and finite-time.
+
+## Suggested Exploration Split
+
+### Exploration A: Freeze packet families and pass/fail sheets
+
+Tasks:
+- choose the anti-circuit and pro-circuit packet families;
+- freeze the admissibility filters, tolerances, thresholds, and diagnostic
+  vectors for all three candidates;
+- record which adverse and favorable cases each family is meant to probe.
+
+Success standard:
+- later outcomes can be read without threshold retuning or packet-family drift.
+
+### Exploration B: Run the anti-circuit dossier
+
+Tasks:
+- test the frozen candidates on adverse cases such as
+  Beltrami cancellation,
+  mirror-mode completion,
+  nearly degenerate triads,
+  and tiny-trigger stress;
+- compute the exact desired-channel versus spectator-channel data and any
+  relevant event-time traces on the fixed window;
+- record candidate-by-candidate failures, survivals, or ambiguities.
+
+Success standard:
+- the dossier produces a clean obstruction-facing read rather than rhetoric
+  about generic entanglement.
+
+### Exploration C: Run the pro-circuit dossier and write the Step-5 readiness verdict
+
+Only run this after Exploration A has frozen the burden currency.
+
+Tasks:
+- test the same candidates on the most honest pro-circuit-friendly families:
+  engineered sign patterns,
+  sparse triad geometries,
+  scale separation,
+  or families with potentially negligible leakage;
+- compare those outcomes against the anti-circuit dossier without changing the
+  packet sheet or thresholds;
+- decide whether Chain Step 5 should start, and if so what one-pass repair
+  targets remain.
+
+Success standard:
+- mission control receives a clean
+  `Step 5 can start`
+  or
+  `branch stops at exact-packet testing`
+  verdict.
+
+## Kill Conditions
+
+Trigger an early negative conclusion for this step if any of the following
+happens:
+
+- no surviving candidate can be evaluated on explicit exact packets without
+  hidden global regularity input, uncontrolled asymptotics, or rhetorical
+  threshold shifts;
+- the anti-circuit / pro-circuit families cannot be stated concretely on the
+  frozen packet object and burden currency;
+- any apparent survivor requires changing packet semantics, spectator classes,
+  sign / phase bookkeeping, or the finite window after outcomes are inspected;
+- the itinerary candidate survives only by importing Tao's averaged one-way
+  behavior rather than remaining an exact-NS admission filter.
+
+If any of those occur, report the sharpest earned negative result and recommend
+that the branch stop before Chain Step 5.
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Do **not** perform the Step-5 repair round yet.
+- Do **not** collapse this step into one soft aggregate score.
+- Do **not** replace the frozen spectator partition or interaction currency.
+- Do **not** claim a theorem or counterexample beyond the audited packet
+  families.
+- Do **not** rescue ambiguous outcomes with ad hoc threshold tightening unless
+  that repair target is merely identified for Step 5 instead of applied now.
+
