+# Step 5 Goal: Chain Step 5 Revise, Split, Or Discard Candidates After One Honest Repair Pass
+
+## Mission Context
+
+**Mission:** Exact NS No-Near-Closed Tao Circuit
+
+**Active chain:**
+`Canonical Winning Chain - Co-Evolving Definition Freeze and Exact Interaction Audit With Invariant Downstream Gates`
+
+**Why this step exists now:** `step-004` kept the branch alive at the exact-
+packet stage. It did not produce a branch-kill or mission-kill. Instead it
+found that
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+and
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+survive the frozen anti-circuit / pro-circuit dossier, while
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`
+remains ambiguous for one sharply named reason:
+the scale-separated friendly family does not yet have a uniformly fixed exact
+`t_next` trace on the current local record.
+Mission control therefore keeps the current chain active. The next unresolved
+bottleneck is no longer whether explicit exact packets can be tested at all. It
+is whether one honest repair pass can turn the Step-4 survivor set into a clean
+shortlist with earned judgments on
+`precision`,
+`robustness`,
+and
+`usefulness`.
+
+## This Step Covers
+
+This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 5 only**.
+
+You must do all of the following, and only the following:
+
+- take the Step-4 classifications as fixed inputs:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure` survives,
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` survives,
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` remains ambiguous;
+- permit exactly one honest repair pass on that Step-4 record;
+- for `Template-Defect Near-Closure`, allow repair only by tightening
+  `lambda_tmpl` and `lambda_spec` using the already recorded anti/pro margins;
+- for `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, allow repair only by tightening
+  `Lambda_tot` and the class budgets using the already recorded anti/pro gap;
+- for `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`, allow repair only by splitting the
+  candidate into
+  `pre-trigger delay filter`
+  and
+  `next-stage transfer-start filter`,
+  or else discarding it if that split cannot remove the scale-separated event
+  ambiguity without changing the window or threshold language;
+- classify every post-repair candidate separately on the three axes:
+  `precision`,
+  `robustness`,
+  and
+  `usefulness`;
+- reject any survivor whose downstream gate is still vague, cosmetic, or
+  bookkeeping-dependent; and
+- decide whether Chain Step 6 is now well-posed as the downstream-object freeze,
+  or whether the branch instead stops here with the sharpest earned negative
+  memo.
+
+Do **not** run Chain Step 6 yet. That belongs to Chain Step 6. Do **not**
+reopen broad planning, substitute a new candidate family, change the packet
+sheet, or perform a fresh exact-packet search. This step is a repair and
+classification pass on the existing dossier, not a new branch.
+
+## Frozen Commitments You Must Inherit
+
+All Step-5 work must inherit the earlier freezes plus the Step-4 dossier:
+
+- the packet object remains the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical
+  packet family with mandatory conjugate completion;
+- the shared Tao-like interaction core remains
+  `A -> B`,
+  `A -> C`,
+  `B,C -> C`,
+  `C,A <-> D`,
+  `D,D -> E`;
+- the forced spectator classes remain:
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  `cross`;
+- the Step-4 test families remain the reference dossier:
+  `F_BM`,
+  `F_DT(delta, eta)`,
+  `F_SS(mu)`,
+  `F_SL(rho)`;
+- the finite activation window, canonical gauge, role order, conjugate
+  convention, sign sheet, and phase anchor remain frozen;
+- threshold movement is allowed only in the two explicitly authorized
+  tightening repairs above, and only by using the already recorded Step-4
+  anti/pro margins rather than new ad hoc tuning;
+- no repair may import Tao's averaged freedoms by hand; and
+- later negative conclusions are still allowed to land only in:
+  `not well-defined`,
+  `not robust after canonicalization`,
+  or `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`.
+
+No repair may rescue a candidate by changing packet semantics, spectator
+partition, interaction currency, sign bookkeeping, phase bookkeeping, the time
+window, or the meaning of the event language after outcomes are seen.
+
+## Required Deliverables
+
+Produce all of the following inside `RESULTS.md`:
+
+1. **Repair ledger**
+   - for each Step-4 candidate, state the inherited Step-4 status,
+     the only repair action allowed,
+     and the exact Step-4 evidence being used;
+   - if a threshold is tightened, state the old value, the new value, and the
+     anti/pro margin or gap that justifies it;
+   - if a split is attempted on `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`, state the two
+     resulting notions exactly and which part of the Step-4 ambiguity each one
+     is meant to isolate.
+
+2. **Revised candidate dossier**
+   - for each repaired, split, unchanged, or discarded candidate, restate the
+     exact criterion and downstream gate on the same frozen packet sheet;
+   - show how the Step-4 dossier now reads under that repaired criterion
+     without introducing new packet families or retuning after the fact;
+   - state whether the candidate is
+     `survives`,
+     `fails`,
+     `discarded`,
+     or
+     `split into ...`.
+
+3. **Three-axis classification table**
+   - classify each post-repair candidate on
+     `precision`,
+     `robustness`,
+     and
+     `usefulness`;
+   - give one short reason per axis tied to the Step-4 dossier or the repair
+     logic rather than a slogan;
+   - state whether any negative result now fully lands in
+     `not well-defined`,
+     `not robust after canonicalization`,
+     or
+     `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`.
+
+4. **Downstream-gate check**
+   - for each surviving candidate, name one concrete downstream theorem or
+     counterexample gate that is now honest enough to freeze in Chain Step 6;
+   - name the smallest meaningful test object or parameter family and the
+     invariant observable or admissibility sheet that Step 6 should carry
+     forward;
+   - reject any candidate whose supposed downstream gate is still vague,
+     cosmetic, or bookkeeping-dependent.
+
+5. **Step verdict**
+   - state whether Chain Step 6 is now well-posed;
+   - if yes, list the surviving candidate set and the exact object-freeze tasks
+     that Chain Step 6 must perform next;
+   - if no, state plainly that the branch should stop here and name the earned
+     negative memo or mission failure bucket.
+
+## Exploration Scope
+
+Use **2-3 explorations total** unless a kill condition fires early.
+
+The work should rely first on the local record already frozen by the previous
+steps:
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN-HISTORY.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/winning-chain.md`
+- the inherited `atlas-source/` packet already used in Steps 1 through 4
+
+Do **not** reopen broad mission planning. Do **not** resurvey Tao's paper
+generally. Do **not** add new packet families or new windows. This step should
+repair and classify only on the frozen dossier already earned.
+
+## Suggested Exploration Split
+
+### Exploration A: Lock the authorized repair sheet
+
+Tasks:
+- extract the exact anti/pro margins and class gaps from Step 4;
+- decide whether the two threshold-based candidates can be tightened honestly
+  without changing their meaning;
+- write the no-retuning discipline for the repair pass.
+
+Success standard:
+- any threshold change is fully justified by the existing dossier and cannot be
+  mistaken for post hoc gerrymandering.
+
+### Exploration B: Resolve the itinerary ambiguity
+
+Tasks:
+- decide whether `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` should be split or discarded;
+- if splitting is honest, define
+  `pre-trigger delay filter`
+  and
+  `next-stage transfer-start filter`
+  on the same frozen event language;
+- test whether either split notion still has a non-cosmetic downstream gate.
+
+Success standard:
+- the behavior-based branch ends this step as either an earned survivor set or
+  an earned discard, not a vague maybe.
+
+### Exploration C: Freeze the shortlist and Step-6 readiness verdict
+
+Only run this after Exploration A and any needed Exploration B work.
+
+Tasks:
+- assemble the final post-repair candidate table;
+- classify each candidate on
+  `precision`,
+  `robustness`,
+  and
+  `usefulness`;
+- decide whether Chain Step 6 should start, and if so what exact object-freeze
+  tasks it should inherit.
+
+Success standard:
+- mission control receives a clean
+  `Step 6 can start`
+  or
+  `branch stops after the repair pass`
+  verdict.
+
+## Kill Conditions
+
+Trigger an early negative conclusion for this step if any of the following
+happens:
+
+- all candidates fail all three axes after the one honest repair pass;
+- any apparent survivor still depends on circular importation of Tao's averaged
+  construction;
+- any repair requires changing packet semantics, spectator classes, sign sheet,
+  phase gauge, interaction currency, or the finite window;
+- a threshold update cannot be justified directly from the Step-4 anti/pro
+  margins or class gaps already on the record;
+- the itinerary split cannot remove the `F_SL(rho)` ambiguity without retuning
+  the window or event-language thresholds; or
+- any surviving candidate's downstream gate remains vague, cosmetic, or
+  bookkeeping-dependent.
+
+If any of those occur, report the sharpest earned negative result and recommend
+that the branch stop before Chain Step 6.
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Do **not** perform the Chain-Step-6 object freeze yet.
+- Do **not** rerun the branch as a new exact-packet search.
+- Do **not** widen scope beyond one repair pass on the Step-4 dossier.
+- Do **not** rescue candidates with ad hoc threshold retuning or new packet
+  semantics.
+- Do **not** generalize beyond the audited packet families and packet class.
+
+## Validation Requirements
+
+- Tag each major conclusion as `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+- Keep branch-level and mission-level claims separate.
+- Make explicit whether each negative judgment is a discard of one candidate or
+  a stop signal for the whole branch.

