+# Step 9 Goal: Chain Step 1 Freeze The Inherited Ledger, Provenance Burden, Remaining Freedoms, And Claim Scope
+
+## Mission Context
+
+**Mission:** Exact NS No-Near-Closed Tao Circuit
+
+**Active chain:**
+`Canonical Winning Chain - Exact One-Bridge Closure Audit With Provenance, Cancellation, And Scope Control`
+
+**Why this step exists now:** `decision-012` already closed the old
+`F_SS(1/12)`
+dynamic-audit branch after
+`step-008`
+showed that the frozen record supports only a classwise exact-closure picture,
+not one finite honest exact closed subsystem. Planning run
+`run-003`
+selected a new chain aimed directly at that gap. Before any recursive closure
+operator, coefficient ledger, or cancellation theorem can be trusted, the
+strategizer must first freeze one audited realization protocol, its exact
+source authority, the freedoms that remain open, and the maximum scope of any
+later claim.
+
+## This Step Covers
+
+This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 1 only**:
+
+`Freeze The Inherited Ledger, Provenance Burden, Remaining Freedoms, And Claim Scope`
+
+You must do all of the following, and only the following:
+
+- import as fixed background everything the mission has already frozen about
+  the canonical one-bridge packet ledger:
+  role labels,
+  mandatory conjugate completion,
+  normalization,
+  the sign and phase sheet,
+  the desired Tao-like core,
+  and the classwise forced-extra categories already earned by
+  `step-008`;
+- state exactly what is still unfrozen and relevant to exact closure for the
+  audited realization:
+  explicit wavevector family,
+  helicity choices,
+  amplitude and phase freedoms,
+  possible coefficient-zero subvarieties,
+  and the finite-closure convention;
+- separate inherited packet semantics from any newly imposed realization
+  restrictions, and say explicitly whether the audit is about one single
+  realization or an explicitly parameterized family;
+- require that every realization datum or exact coefficient identity intended
+  for later promoted use comes with one same-currency promoted derivation or
+  explicit citation path;
+- declare the maximum claim scope in advance:
+  one audited realization,
+  one audited family,
+  or the full one-bridge class only if a genuine reduction argument is later
+  proved;
+- if these locks cannot be maintained honestly, stop and package a
+  source-basis / no-canonical-finite-reduction memo rather than pushing to
+  recursive closure.
+
+Do **not** do Chain Step 2 work yet. In particular, do **not**:
+
+- build the recursive closure operator;
+- compute the full exact coefficient ledger;
+- audit cancellation regimes;
+- prove any obstruction theorem or loophole family;
+- promote repaired
+  `G_tmpl`
+  or repaired
+  `G_leak`
+  into closure-implication language; or
+- reopen broad mission planning or compare unrelated branches.
+
+## Frozen Commitments You Must Inherit
+
+All Step-9 work must inherit the following mission-control locks:
+
+- `step-008` remains a real negative on the prior branch:
+  the record there earned only classwise exact non-isolability /
+  arbitrary-truncation requirement,
+  not a finite exact closed subsystem ready for dynamics;
+- the canonical one-bridge packet semantics already frozen on the ledger stay
+  fixed unless the step concludes they cannot be maintained honestly under the
+  new audit;
+- any newly used realization data, wavevector-level arithmetic, or exact
+  coefficient formula must have one same-currency promoted derivation or
+  explicit citation path;
+- no theorem statement may outrun the audited realization or audited family
+  unless a genuine reduction argument is proved later;
+- if no theorem-ready closure object is eventually frozen, the branch may
+  conclude only a negative or scope-control memo, not a closure-implication
+  theorem;
+- draft logs, stale threshold sheets, and hand-entered checkers may assist
+  orientation but cannot become theorem authority by implication.
+
+This step may refine the realization data and scope. It may **not** quietly
+change the inherited packet semantics, remove known freedoms without saying so,
+or smuggle in an ad hoc closure convention just to make later steps look more
+tractable.
+
+## Required Deliverables
+
+Produce all of the following inside `RESULTS.md`:
+
+1. **Inherited fixed ledger**
+   - list the exact one-bridge ingredients already frozen by the mission
+     record;
+   - distinguish inherited packet semantics from conclusions that only hold for
+     the old
+     `F_SS(1/12)`
+     witness-local branch;
+   - state what Step 1 is allowed to reuse without new proof.
+
+2. **Audited realization definition**
+   - freeze one explicit audited realization or one explicitly parameterized
+     audited family;
+   - list the wavevector data, helicity choices, conjugation constraints,
+     amplitude and phase freedoms, and any declared finite-closure convention;
+   - identify any coefficient-zero or degeneracy subvarieties that must be
+     tracked later rather than assumed away.
+
+3. **Provenance and source-basis table**
+   - for each realization datum and each exact coefficient identity needed
+     later, name the same-currency promoted derivation or citation path that
+     authorizes it;
+   - separate promoted authority from draft or non-authoritative helper
+     material;
+   - state plainly if any required source basis is missing.
+
+4. **Scope declaration**
+   - declare the maximum claim scope that later chain steps may use;
+   - explain why broader scope is not yet licensed;
+   - state what repaired
+     `G_tmpl`
+     and repaired
+     `G_leak`
+     are and are not allowed to imply on this audited ledger at this stage.
+
+5. **Step verdict**
+   - say whether Chain Step 2 is now well posed on an honest audited object;
+   - if yes, list exactly what Chain Step 2 must inherit unchanged;
+   - if no, state that the branch stops here with a source-basis or
+     no-canonical-finite-reduction memo.
+
+## Exploration Scope
+
+Use **2-3 explorations total** unless a kill condition fires early.
+
+Start from the active mission record:
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/MISSION.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN-HISTORY.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/controller/decisions/decision-012.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-003/final-decider.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-003/winning-chain.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-008/RESULTS.md`
+
+Then use only the older local sources needed to recover the inherited canonical
+packet semantics, the frozen sign / phase / normalization sheet, and the
+classwise forced-extra categories already on the record.
+
+Do **not** reopen earlier mission stages broadly. Do **not** do fresh exact
+closure enumeration yet. Do **not** let convenience choose the realization
+without recording what freedom was used.
+
+## Suggested Exploration Split
+
+### Exploration A: Recover the inherited fixed ledger
+
+Tasks:
+
+- extract the exact packet semantics, normalization, desired core, and
+  classwise forced-extra categories already frozen on the local record;
+- separate those from witness-local conclusions tied only to the invalidated
+  old branch;
+- list the open variables that the new audited realization must still freeze.
+
+Success standard:
+
+- the branch starts from one honest inherited ledger instead of mixing
+  classwide facts with witness-local artifacts.
+
+### Exploration B: Freeze one audited realization and provenance table
+
+Tasks:
+
+- specify one explicit realization or one explicit audited family;
+- attach same-currency authority to every later-critical datum;
+- declare the finite-closure convention and any tracked exceptional sets;
+- state the maximum claim scope.
+
+Success standard:
+
+- later steps can cite one audited object and one authority table without
+  post hoc repairs.
+
+### Exploration C: Write the Step-1 stop-or-handoff memo
+
+Only run this after the first two explorations settle the object.
+
+Tasks:
+
+- assemble the realization-and-provenance memo for
+  `RESULTS.md`;
+- decide whether Chain Step 2 is honestly well posed;
+- if not, package the negative memo immediately.
+
+Success standard:
+
+- mission control receives either one audited object ready for recursive
+  closure work or one clean Step-1 failure memo.
+
+## Kill Conditions
+
+Trigger an early negative conclusion for this step if any of the following
+happens:
+
+- making the realization explicit changes the inherited packet semantics rather
+  than instantiating them;
+- the step quietly removes known freedoms, degeneracies, or exceptional sets in
+  order to simplify later closure claims;
+- the finite-closure convention is ad hoc, undefined, or not frozen clearly
+  enough for later recursive audit;
+- any later-critical realization datum or coefficient identity lacks promoted
+  same-currency provenance;
+- the step cannot state an honest maximum claim scope without overreaching.
+
+If a kill condition fires, stop at Step 1 and package the negative memo. Do
+not advance to recursive closure bookkeeping.

